  "title": "Embryologist/ Senior Embryologist",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary:</strong></p>\n<p>We are seeking a dedicated and Clinical Embryologist to join our dynamic team. The successful candidate will be responsible for performing andrology and embryology procedures in compliance with established protocols and quality standards.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<p>Perform clinical embryology and andrology duties following laboratory protocols and professional standards.</p>\n<p>Conduct routine diagnostic services and laboratory procedures aligned with IVF practices.</p>\n<p>Manage supplies and handle equipment required for ART procedures.</p>\n<p>Adhere to quality control measures, ethical standards, and regulatory guidelines in the handling of gametes and embryos.</p>\n<p>Maintain a safe and sterile laboratory environment in accordance with SOPs.</p>\n<p>Conduct calibration, daily checks, and preventive maintenance of laboratory equipment.</p>\n<p>Accurately collect, maintain, and report laboratory statistics.</p>\n<p>Participate in patient and staff education sessions and relevant team meetings.</p>\n<p>Perform internal and external quality control and assurance testing.</p>\n<p>Undertake additional laboratory-related duties as assigned.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<p>1. Possess a Degree in Clinical Embryology, Biomedical Science, Life Sciences or its equivalent.</p>\n<p>2. At least 2 years of relevant working experience.</p>\n<p>3. Proficient in laboratory skills and policies specific to IVF procedures.</p>\n<p>4. Able to work independently and as a team.</p>\n<p>5. Have excellent manual dexterity and the ability to pay attention to detail.</p>\n<p>6. Possess strong interpersonal skills to work collaboratively with others.</p>\n<p>7. Able to communicate effectively.</p>\n<p>8. Due to the nature of work, flexibility in schedule is a requirement.</p>",
